ReconcileHelpTitle=How mismatch resolution works
ReconcileHelpPoint1=Review the Diff column first. A positive Diff means Dolibarr is short and the tool will create an additional invoice for that amount.
ReconcileHelpPoint2=A negative Diff means Dolibarr is high and the tool will create a credit note for the absolute value of that amount.
ReconcileHelpPoint3=Use the Notes column to add an optional internal note for that row. The note is saved with the current reconcile session and included on created Dolibarr documents.
ReconcileHelpPoint4=Refund-led rows are compared differently: the negative eBay refund net is added to the Dolibarr net. Regular sale rows still use eBay net minus Dolibarr net.

